erham Cars|Caterham]] (1973)\n*[[Caterpillar Inc.|Caterpillar]] (1925)\n*[[Changan Automobile|Chang'an]] (1862)\n*[[Changfeng Motor|Changfeng]] (1950)\n*[[Changhe]] (1970)\n*[[Chery]] (1997)\n*[[Chevrolet]] (1911)\n*[[Chrysler]] (1925)\n*[[Citro\u00ebn]] (1919)\n*[[Cizeta]] (1988)\n*[[Coda Automotive|Coda]] (2009)\n*[[w:de:Corvette|Corvette]] (2005)\n*[[SEAT Sport (Cupra)|CUPRA]] (1985/2018)\n*[[Czinger 21C|Czinger]] (2019)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==D==\n{{Div col|colwidth=14em}}\n*[[Automobile Dacia|Dacia]] (1966)\n*[[Daihatsu]] (1951)\n*[[Datsun]] (1931)\n*[[De La Chapelle|De la Chapelle]] (1970s)\n*[[DeLorean Motor Company (Texas)|DeLorean]] (1975)\n*[[DeSoto (automobile)|DeSoto]]  (1928)\n*[[Devon Motorworks|Devon]] (2008)\n*[[De Tomaso]] (1959)\n*[[Detroit Electric]] (1907)\n*[[Diardi]] (1987)\n*[[Dodge]] (1900)\n*[[Dongfeng Motor|Dongfeng]] (1969)\n*[[Donkervoort]] (1978)\n*[[Donto Motors|Donto]] (2010)\n*[[DR Automobiles|DR Automobiles]] (2006)\n*[[DS Automobiles]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/motor-shows-geneva-motor-show/ds-launched-stand-alone-brand-geneva-motor-show|title=DS launched as stand-alone brand at Geneva motor show|publisher=Autocar Magazine|date=3 March 2015|accessdate=6 March 2015}}</ref> (2015)\n*[[Dynasty IT|Dynasty]] (2001)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==E==\n{{Div col|colwidth=14em}}\n*[[E-VADE]]<ref>http://www.evade.com.au/evade.php</ref> (2008)\n*[[Effedi]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.italiaspeed.com/2006/cars/other/effedi/05/maranello4/2105.html|title=italiaspeed.com|publisher=}}</ref> (1979) \n*[[Egy-Tech Engineering|Egy-Tech]] (1997)\n*[[Electric Raceabout]] (2009)\n*[[Elfin Sports Cars|Elfin]] (1957)\n*[[Elio Motors|Elio]] (2009)\n*[[Geely#Englon|Englon]] (2010)\n*[[Esemka]] (2007)\n*[[Etox]] (2006)\n*[[Equus Automotive|Equus]] (2009)\n*[[Exagon Furtive-eGT|Exagon]] (2009)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==F==\n{{Div col|colwidth=14em}}\n*[[FAW Group|FAW]] (1953)\n*[[Ferrari]] (1939)\n*[[Fiat Automobiles|Fiat]] (1899)\n*[[Fiat Prof